413 template <typename T>
414 class WeakCallbackInfo {
415  public:
416  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
417 
418  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
419  void* internal_fields[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback],
420  Callback* callback)
421  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
422  for (int i = 0; i < kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
423  internal_fields_[i] = internal_fields[i];
424  }
425  }
426 
427  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
428  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
429  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
430 
431  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
432  void* GetInternalField1() const) {
433  return internal_fields_[0];
434  }
435  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
436  void* GetInternalField2() const) {
437  return internal_fields_[1];
438  }
439 
440  V8_DEPRECATED("Not realiable once SetSecondPassCallback() was used.",
441  bool IsFirstPass() const) {
442  return callback_ != nullptr;
443  }
444 
445  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
446  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
447  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
448  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
449  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
450  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
451  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
452 
453  private:
454  Isolate* isolate_;
455  T* parameter_;
456  Callback* callback_;
457  void* internal_fields_[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback];
458 };

460 
461 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
462 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
463 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
464 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
465 // possible to request a second pass callback.
466 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };

5454 enum RAILMode {
5455  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
5456  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
5457  // Throughput may be throttled.
5458  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
5459  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
5460  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
5461  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
5462  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
5463  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
5464  // in this mode.
5465  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
5466  // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
5467  // turn off latency optimizations.
5468  PERFORMANCE_LOAD
5469 };

6946 template <class T>
6947 class Maybe {
6948  public:
6949  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
6950  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
6951 
6952  // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
6953  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
6954 
6955  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
6956  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
6957  return IsJust();
6958  }
6959 
6960  // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
6961  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
6962  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
6963  return value_;
6964  }
6965 
6966  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
6967  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
6968  }
6969 
6970  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
6971  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
6972  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
6973  }
6974 
6975  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
6976  return !operator==(other);
6977  }
6978 
6979  private:
6980  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}

7519 const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
7520 const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
7521 const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
7522 
7523 // Tag information for HeapObject.
7524 const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
7525 const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
7526 const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
7527 
7528 // Tag information for Smi.
7529 const int kSmiTag = 0;
7530 const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
7531 const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
7532 
7533 template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
7534 
7535 template<int kSmiShiftSize>
7536 V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7537  int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7538  uintptr_t tagged_value =
7539  (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
7540  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
7541 }
7542 
7543 // Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
7544 template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
7545  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
7546  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
7547  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
7548  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
7549  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7550  // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
7551  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
7552  }
7553  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7554  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
7555  }
7556  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7557  // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
7558  // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
7559  // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
7560  // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
7561  //
7562  // CAUTION: The original code below:
7563  // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
7564  // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
7565  // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
7566  // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
7567  // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
7568  return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
7569  }
7570 };
7571 
7572 // Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
7573 template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
7574  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
7575  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
7576  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
7577  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
7578  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7579  // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
7580  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
7581  }
7582  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7583  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
7584  }
7585  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7586  // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
7587  return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
7588  }
7589 };
7590

7592 const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
7593 const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
7594 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
7595 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }

8249 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
8250 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8251  typedef internal::Object O;
8252  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
8253  typedef internal::Internals I;
8254  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
8255  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
8256  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
8257  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
8258  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
8259  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType) {
8260  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8261  O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
8262  O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
8263  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
8264  }
8265 #endif
8266  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
8267 }
8268 
8269 
8270 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
8271 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8272  typedef internal::Object O;
8273  typedef internal::Internals I;
8274  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
8275  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
8276  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
8277  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
8278  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
8279  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType)) {
8280  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8281  return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
8282  }
8283 #endif
8284  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
8285 }

8836  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
